HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 306
By Boyd
A RESOLUTION to recognize and commend the founding of the
Major David Wilson Chapter of The Sons of the
American Revolution.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly take great pleasure in recognizing
those outstanding civic organizations and their members who work with purpose, commitment,
and enthusiasm to promote patriotism and preserve America's panoramic history and heritage;
and
WHEREAS, one such worthy organization is the Major David Wilson Chapter of The
Sons of the American Revolution, which was granted a charter on January 25, 2025, by the
Tennessee Society Sons of the American Revolution Board of Governors at their regional
meeting in Jackson; and
WHEREAS, the Sons of the American Revolution (SAR) is a patriotic, historical, and
educational organization composed of male descendants of those who supported the American
Revolution; members can trace their lineage back to individuals who either fought in the
Revolutionary War, served in the Continental Congress, or contributed in other ways to the
cause of American Independence; and
WHEREAS, the SAR was established in 1889 and has grown to include chapters across
the United States and internationally, playing a key role in fostering a deeper understanding of
American history and honoring the legacy of those who fought for independence; the SAR is
also involved in the preservation of history, education, patriotic activities, and community
service; and
WHEREAS, the Major David Wilson Chapter of the SAR is named in honor of a native of
North Carolina who enlisted in the Rowan County Regiment of the North Carolina Militia under
