Colonel Francis Locke; his journey in the Revolutionary War was distinguished by his
participation in several critical battles and engagements; and
WHEREAS, later in life, Major Wilson moved to what is now Sumner County, where he
was very involved in local government and served as the first Speaker of the House for the
territory that would later become the State of Tennessee; he is also the namesake of Wilson
County; and
WHEREAS, the first officers of the Major David Wilson Chapter of the SAR were sworn
in on February 15, 2025, in a ceremony in Lebanon; the founding members of this newly
established chapter are George Richard Bouton, Eugene Wade Bland, Isaac Lewis Bland, John
Robert Emmert, James Howard Jordan, James Howard Murff, Edward Wayne Patton, Jerry
Allen Vance, and Dannell Bennett Waters; and
WHEREAS, the charter members of the Major David Wilson Chapter of the SAR are
Haywood St. Clair Barry, William Rex Bouton, Damon Clark Boyd, Paul Wayne Devine, Robert
Coleman Fields, James Bradley Jordan, Jon Todd Hannah, Daniel Edward Hardison, David
Floyd Howell, Jerry Gordon Hughes, James Chase Lannom, James David Peyton, David Melvin
Roberts, Dwight Groom Saddler, Raymond Shane Stroud, Paul Calvert Stumb, Bruce Carleton
Taylor, Eddie Linn Tomlinson, James Christopher Vance, Kevin Oakley Vance, Michael Ryan
Vance, Timothy Owen White, and William O'Neill Whisenant; and
WHEREAS, the newly established Major David Wilson Chapter of the SAR is dedicated
to preserving American history and fostering patriotism, and it is wholly fitting that this worthy
organization should be honored at this time; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we recognize and commend the founding of the Major David Wilson
Chapter of the Sons of the American Revolution, expressing our gratitude to its members for
